5:
The hell's up with these things? The
way they multiply gives me the
creeps.
9:
We've gotta clean this up as fast as
we can. Let's do this!
22:
Are you chasing your dreams,
everyone?
26:
Nothing's more real than the
dreams you cherish most! Here
comes Laputina!
32: Whoooa! It's Lap-T! It's really her!
36:
...Huh, what? Are we the only ones
out of the loop?
40:
I'm an idol, aren't I? Of course I'll
sing! But first...
44:
I've got a little hero work to wrap up
first!
49:
Today's performance was brought
to you by INOBEC. Please follow and
share with #Lap-T!
53:
Dunno what's going on here, but...
damn. This is something.
62:
Hey, you guys! Thanks for the assist
today. I was pretty shocked to see
organics as strong as you!
67:
Oh, uh... Not at all. We probably
would've been in a lot of trouble if
you hadn't swooped in.
71:
As long as I could help keep
everyone's dreams alive, I'm happy!
80:
I'm Laputina, guardian of the
dreams of all people everywhere!
89: Stop buying into this sales pitch.
95:
It's not a sales pitch! I'm really
serious!
98:
...I know that's hard to believe. A lot
of people who talk like this have
ulterior motives.
102:
But don't worry, okay? If you never
give up, eventually your dreams will
come true! After all, I'll always be
cheering you on!
105:
CHASE MY DREAM! CHASE YOUR
DREAM! YEAHHHH!
108: O-okay, guess we'll get going now
116:
What's wrong with them?! They just
disrespected Lap-T!
117:
They can't comprehend Lap-T's
sublime wonder... What a bunch of
losers.
120:
Wait... They're friends with that PBC
hero...
126:
Laputina? Oh... Right, the former
social media idol?
133:
She was recently recruited by a major 
prosthetics manufacturer 
to help with sales. 
They're billing her as an "Idol hero."
137:
Idol hero... So you two aren't the
same, then?
141:
I'm... Well, I get treated like an idol sometimes, but I'm still just a hero at
the end of the day.
144:
She's something else, though. She
sings and dances as an idol, but
simultaneously does hero work, too.
149:
...So that's how it is, huh. Was
wondering what the hell was going
on back there.
154:
...So? How was it, seeing her perform
live? Was she cute? She's pretty
petite, right?
162:
An idol hero... How should I describe
her? She seemed like a being from
outside of this world.
167:
Right, yeah. The job of idols in this
city is to create a sort of fantasy
world where the fans can escape
from the pain and worries of reality.
170:
But she... genuinely believes that
everyone's dreams will come true.
173:
She's got a lot of, well... antis online,
but she never gives up. I respect
that.
178:
Wishing for an ideal future is
somewhat like a prayer. I think I can
grasp that concept, to some degree
at least.
181:
Perhaps, more than anyone else,
she simply wants to believe that
such an ideal future could be
realized.
185:
I don't "want to believe" it! I really DO
believe in it!
190:
HUH?! Lap-T? Right here in front of
me, for real?!
194:
I'll never stop helping people
achieve their dreams until there
aren't any dreams left to chase!
That's... what I decided for myself.
198:
You guys are heroes too, right? In
that case... Let's work together for
the same goal!
202:
Why do you want to make
everyone's dreams come true, Lap-T?
206:
Because, if you give up on your
dreams... That's it. There's nothing
left for you. I hate the thought of
someone being like that.
215: I hear you LOUD and clear!
224:
It seems like a collaboration is in
order!
229:
Where ideals collide... Friendship
and understanding brought about
by a joint struggle... Yes, I see a
wonderful story unfolding!
234:
Huh? No, INOBEC is part of Noxel
Group. Wouldn't that be a problem
for us?
238:
That, my dear, is what collaboration
is all about! Don't worry, a contract
with the other party has already
been signed. They were delighted
with the opportunity!
241:
What do you say, Idol Hero? You
have nothing to lose, and everything
to gain!
247:
...All right! Let me show you guys that
I'm in the right!
252:
H-huh? Wait... Really? I wasn't ready
for this at all! C'mon Alk, say
something!
262:
HEY! Don't act like this isn't your
problem!
267:
Welcome, Lap-T. We're happy to
have you.
274:
Wowwww! This is the perfect place
to take a photo for my next post!
278:
D-don't share anything! You mustn't
forget the nondisclosure agreement!
286:
Another world, huh... So many more
people I can help.
290:
I've made up my mind! I'm going to
help everyone's dreams come true
OUTSIDE of my world, too!
